orary objects must be used immediately, as they are destroyed at the end of the full expression in which they are created.Related contentWe discussstd::stringandstd::string_viewliterals in lesson5.7 -- Introduction to std::stringand5.8 -- Introduction to std::string_viewrespectively.Magic numbersAmagic numberis a literal (usually a number) that either has an unclear meaning or may need to be changed later.Here are two statements showing examples of magic numbers:const int maxStudentsPerSchool{ numClassrooms * 30 };
